cast_shell: size CastContentWindow at CreateWindow time

Upstream's flow is:

  CastServiceSimple::StartInternal()
    -> CreateWebView
    -> LoadUrl(startup_url_)
    -> GrantScreenAccess()      // window_ is null, no-op
    -> CreateWindow()           // sets window_; never calls SetFullWindowBounds

The actual SetFullWindowBounds call lives in CastContentWindowAura::
DidStartNavigation, which fires only once per CastContentWindow because
resize_window_when_navigation_starts_ flips to false. That works on
production Cast hardware where multi-process timing leaves the observer
attached well before the URL load fires DidStartNavigation. On this
build (single-process + immediate LoadUrl) the navigation can be far
enough along by the time WebContentsObserver attaches that the one
DidStartNavigation event is dropped, leaving the wl_surface at the
default 0x0 bounds and the panel showing the compositor background.

Call SetFullWindowBounds() from CreateWindow() the moment window_ is
non-null. Idempotent with the DidStartNavigation path; covers the
case where the observer missed the event.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [kiosk-specific use case]

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>

--- a/chromecast/browser/cast_content_window_aura.cc
+++ b/chromecast/browser/cast_content_window_aura.cc
@@ -125,6 +125,20 @@
   touch_blocker_ =
       std::make_unique<TouchBlocker>(window_, !params_->enable_touch_input);

+  // bridgething patch: size the WebContents window to the primary
+  // display now, in addition to relying on DidStartNavigation. The
+  // upstream path is: GrantScreenAccess() called before CreateWindow()
+  // (so window_ is null and SetFullWindowBounds is skipped) and then
+  // a single DidStartNavigation event sets bounds when the first
+  // navigation actually fires through the observer. On this build
+  // with --single-process + immediate LoadUrl the early-bound
+  // navigation can land before the WebContentsObserver is attached,
+  // dropping the only resize signal and leaving the wl_surface at
+  // its default 0x0 bounds. Calling SetFullWindowBounds here
+  // guarantees the window picks up the CastScreen primary display
+  // size as soon as window_ exists.
+  SetFullWindowBounds();
+
   if (has_screen_access_) {
     window_->Show();
   } else {
